Here is the **ASCII connection diagram** for the **ZF 8HP45 / 8HP family** as modeled in the corrected `eight_speed.py`.

## 1) Permanent mechanical connection map

```text
                 ZF 8HP45 / 8HP — permanent member connections


                 ┌───────────────────────────────┐
Input ──────────►│ P2 carrier                    │
                 └───────────────────────────────┘


                 ┌───────────────────────────────┐
sun12  ◄────────►│ P1 sun = P2 sun              │
                 └───────────────────────────────┘
                       ▲
                       │
                    A brake
                  (grounds sun12)


                 ┌───────────────────────────────┐
p1r    ◄────────►│ P1 ring                       │
                 └───────────────────────────────┘
                       ▲
                       │
                    B brake
                  (grounds P1 ring)


                 ┌───────────────────────────────┐
p1c_p4r◄────────►│ P1 carrier = P4 ring         │
                 └───────────────────────────────┘


                 ┌───────────────────────────────┐
p23    ◄────────►│ P2 ring = P3 sun             │
                 └───────────────────────────────┘


                 ┌───────────────────────────────┐
c_out  ◄────────►│ P3 ring = P4 sun             │
                 │ (same driven C-side node)     │
                 └───────────────────────────────┘
                       ▲
                       │
                     C clutch
                (Input drives c_out)


                 ┌───────────────────────────────┐
p3c    ◄────────►│ P3 carrier                    │
                 └───────────────────────────────┘
                       ▲
                       │
                     D clutch
                  (ties p3c to output)


                 ┌───────────────────────────────┐
output ◄────────►│ P4 carrier = output shaft    │
                 └───────────────────────────────┘


E clutch connects:
    p23  ◄──────────────────────────────►  c_out
```

---

## 2) Gearset-by-gearset view

This is the same thing, but organized by planetary set.

```text
P1:
    sun    = sun12
    ring   = p1r
    carrier= p1c_p4r

P2:
    sun    = sun12
    ring   = p23
    carrier= input

P3:
    sun    = p23
    ring   = c_out
    carrier= p3c

P4:
    sun    = c_out
    ring   = p1c_p4r
    carrier= output
```

That is really the cleanest compact description of the 8HP topology.

